# Review the Cutover and Retire the Inflated Collection

## Step

Joel reviews the session-index validation report, approves switching `joelclaw sessions search` and other readers to the SQLite session index, and approves dropping `run_chunks_dev` from Typesense entirely (per [the availability decision](./decide-availability-shape.svx), session search leaves Typesense). An explicit rollback plan comes first (diagnosis § Repair the projection) — note the raw JSONL plus manifest can always rebuild the index, so the rollback story should be cheap.

Preconditions before the review, from [adversarial verification of the index](./session-index-verification.svx) (2026-07-20):

1. The append consumer is wired into the patched capture path, with `sessions.db` flipped to WAL mode (it currently sits in `journal_mode=delete`).
2. `joelclaw sessions search` (and any other reader) actually opens `sessions.db`.
3. Typesense parity runs once `/health` is green — or Joel explicitly accepts raw-JSONL-as-truth validation in its place.
4. A grep-proven inventory of every `run_chunks_dev` reader (CLI, web app, Inngest functions) exists, and each is switched or consciously excepted — no reader retired from memory (failure mode #5, 2026-07-20 grilling).
5. The append consumer is proven idempotent under real Inngest at-least-once redelivery and step retries, not just in unit fixtures.

Resolved when readers point at the SQLite index, the rollback plan is written, and Joel has said "retire it" out loud.

## Result (2026-07-20)

Joel reviewed the [cutover packet](./cutover-review-packet.svx) and approved: "approved get it done." All preconditions were satisfied before the ask: append consumer live and proven by canary, readers switched, catch-up at zero pending, real parity measured (449,220 vs 3,570,503 chunks), rollback plan written, reader inventory grep-proven.

Retirement executed in order: the writer's `index-chunks` Typesense import removed and `ensureCollections` stopped recreating the collection (commit `2dd747de`), worker bounced onto the retired path (health 200), then `run_chunks_dev` dropped — 3,570,566 documents, 25 → 24 collections. A post-drop canary capture appended to `sessions.db` with zero worker errors. Pre-drop safety: `sessions.db` SHA-256 saved at `~/.joelclaw/search/sessions.db.sha256.pre-retirement`; raw JSONL and manifest remain authoritative; `backfill-run-typesense.ts` retained as the rebuild path.

The Typesense restart-time receipt was NOT measured — the process runs under another user and steering has no sudo. It rides [the reboot gate](./verify-reboot-gate.svx), or `sudo launchctl kickstart -k system/com.joelclaw.central.typesense` any time Joel wants the number.
